---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = 'Internal Sprint 02 — Signal Normalization';
---

<BaseLayout title={title}>
  <h1>Internal Sprint 02 — Signal Normalization</h1>
</BaseLayout>

<section class="runbook">
  <h1>Internal Sprint 01 — Signal Capture</h1>

  <p class="subtitle">
    Establish deterministic evidence collection across the framework.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <h2>🎯 Objective</h2>
  <p>
    Capture raw, unopinionated signals from the system under test and the automation framework.
    This layer does not interpret — it only observes.
  </p>

  <h2>🧩 System Diagram</h2>

  <pre>
Playwright Execution
        ↓
Validation Commands
        ↓
Validation Log (raw evidence)
  </pre>

  <h2>📦 Inputs</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Playwright test execution</li>
    <li>Framework configuration</li>
    <li>Locator usage patterns</li>
    <li>Artifact generation (trace, video, screenshots)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>📤 Outputs</h2>
  <pre>
validation-output/
  run_all_validation_commands_*.log
  </pre>

  <h2>📏 Acceptance Criteria</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Validation log is always generated</li>
    <li>No silent execution (all commands logged)</li>
    <li>Locator patterns are detectable from logs</li>
    <li>Artifact generation is observable</li>
    <li>Runtime failures are captured</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>⚠️ Failure Modes</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>No log file generated → system blind</li>
    <li>Partial logs → incomplete signal</li>
    <li>Execution succeeds but produces no artifacts</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>🧠 Principles</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Evidence over interpretation</li>
    <li>No assumptions about system health</li>
    <li>Everything must be traceable to raw output</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>🧪 Verification</h2>
  <pre>
ls validation-output/
cat validation-output/run_all_validation_commands_*.log
  </pre>

</section>